# Compiled Python bytecode caches: machine/host-specific, regenerated at
# runtime inside the container, and would only bloat the build context.
__pycache__/
# Individual compiled bytecode files (same rationale as __pycache__/ above,
# in case any stray .pyc files exist outside a __pycache__ directory).
*.pyc
# Local Python virtual environment: host-specific interpreter/paths that
# must never be copied into the image; the image installs its own deps
# via requirements.txt instead.
.venv/
# Pytest's cache directory: local test-run metadata with no purpose inside
# the built container image.
.pytest_cache/
# Test suite source: not needed to run the service in production, so
# excluding it keeps the image smaller and avoids shipping test fixtures.
tests/
# Markdown documentation files: irrelevant to running the service, so kept
# out of the build context/image.
*.md
